    "description": "sinops Inc. develops and sells demand forecasting and automatic ordering service systems for the distribution, food manufacturing, and wholesale industries in Japan. The company offers sinops-CLOUD, a cloud service for inventory, ordering, and forecasting; sinops-CLOUD M, which manages inventory intelligently with optimal ordering of raw and packaging materials; and sinops-WLMS, a human resources maximization AI service that makes people's work visible and support planning and development. It also provides sinops-W, a demand forecasting cash flow optimization system; and sinops-IM, an inter-base transfer instruction optimization system. In addition, it offers logistics diagnosis and improvement, and shelf allocation consulting services; implementation support; and support services. The company was formerly known as Link Inc. and changed its name to sinops Inc. in April 2019. sinops Inc. was incorporated in 1987 and is headquartered in Toyonaka, Japan."
